nse tests |\n\n### 6. AR-039 Design/Spec Documents\n\n**Found:** `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-039/tasks.md`\n\nThis is the task file for **AR-039: Go Unit Tests (router/store/picod)**. Key details:\n- **Module:** `pkg` | **Language:** Go | **Size:** L\n- **Base specs:** `pkg/router/`, `pkg/store/`, `pkg/picod/` source code\n- **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n- **Tasks:** T-1 (router tests), T-2 (store tests), T-3 (picod tests), T-4 (run full test suite)\n- All tasks are currently marked as **TODO** -- this is a skeleton task file awaiting implementation\n- **Dependency graph:** T-1, T-2, T-3 are parallelizable; T-4 depends on all three\n- **Verification commands specified:**\n  - `go test ./pkg/router/... ./pkg/store/... ./pkg/picod/... -v`\n  - `go test ./pkg/router/... ./pkg/store/... ./pkg/picod/... -coverprofile=coverage.out`\n  - `go tool cover -func=coverage.out`\n  - `go test ./pkg/router/... ./pkg/store/... ./pkg/picod/... -race`\n  - `go vet ./pkg/router/... ./pkg/store/... ./pkg/picod/...`\n\n**No ST-3 specific files found** -- the reference to ST-3 is only as a precondition note in the AR-039 tasks.md.\n\n### 7. Testing Conventions Observed\n\nThe project follows consistent, well-established Go testing patterns:\n\n**Test Framework:**\n- Uses `github.com/stretchr/testify` exclusively (`assert` and `require` packages)\n- No table-driven tests observed; each test case is a separate `TestXxx` function\n- Subtests via `t.Run()` are not used\n\n**Test Setup Patterns:**\n- `t.TempDir()` for temporary directories (auto-cleaned)\n- `t.Helper()` on test helper functions\n- `t.Cleanup()` for resource cleanup (e.g., closing miniredis, redis clients)\n- `os.Setenv()`/`os.Unsetenv()` with `defer` for environment variable tests\n- `gin.SetMode(gin.TestMode)` before creating gin engines\n\n**HTTP Testing:**\n- `net/http/httptest.NewRequest()` + `httptest.NewRecorder()` pattern\n- Direct `engine.ServeHTTP(w, req)` calls (no actual HTTP server)\n- JSON response parsing via `json.Unmarshal(w.Body.Bytes(), &resp)`\n\n**Assertion Patterns:**\n- `require.NoError(t, err)` for fatal errors (stops test)\n- `assert.Equal(t, expected, actual)` for value comparisons\n- `assert.ErrorIs(t, err, ErrXxx)` for sentinel error matching\n- `assert.Contains(t, err.Error(), \"substring\")` for error message content\n- `require.NotNil(t, x)` / `assert.Nil(t, x)` for nil checks\n- `assert.Same(t, a, b)` for pointer identity checks\n\n**Test Helper Functions:**\n- `newTestRedisStore(t)` / `newTestValkeyStore(t)` -- factory functions returning store + miniredis\n- `testSandboxInfo(sessionID)` -- fixture factory for SandboxInfo\n- `generateTestPrivateKey(t)` / `generateTestPublicKey(t)` / `signTestToken(t)` -- crypto helpers in picod\n- `authedRequest(t, server, method, path, body)` -- helper for authenticated HTTP requests in picod\n- `setupTestRouter(jwtManager)` -- router setup helper\n\n**Naming Conventions:**\n- `TestPackageName_FunctionName_Scenario` pattern (e.g., `TestRedisStore_GetSandbox_NotFound`)\n- `TestConstants_ConstantName` for constant value tests\n- `TestPackageName_InterfaceCompliance` for interface assertion tests (`var _ Store = (*redisStore)(nil)`)\n\n**Mocking Strategy:**\n- `github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2` for Redis/Valkey testing (in-memory Redis emulator)\n- No interface-based mocking; tests use real implementations with in-memory backends\n- Environment variable manipulation for configuration testing\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_284a6c1f2ffev6J4XvFTS0vSwh","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775890939402,"end":1775891091088}}}}
