{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775891285125,"sessionID":"ses_284a6e951ffebDLiZeeUxpPxrL","part":{"id":"prt_d7b5cb54f001dN3T56DsfYrOeV","messageID":"msg_d7b5c4db9001lLAiwkscotUr4a","sessionID":"ses_284a6e951ffebDLiZeeUxpPxrL","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_477407d720874d8aa00f3669","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-039: Go 单元测试 (router/store/picod) — Tasks\n\n**Module:** `pkg` | **Language:** Go | **Size:** L\n**Base specs:** `pkg/router/`, `pkg/store/`, `pkg/picod/` source code\n**Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n\n---\n\n## T-1: router/backend.go — Backend & HealthChecker\n\n- [ ] `TestBackend_String` — `String()` returns formatted `\"Backend{URL: ..., Healthy: ...}\"`\n- [ ] `TestNewBackendHealthChecker_Defaults` — constructor sets interval, fail/success thresholds, default checker\n- [ ] `TestBackendHealthChecker_Check_Success` — mock checker returns true → `ConsecutiveSuccess` increments, `Healthy` becomes true after threshold\n- [ ] `TestBackendHealthChecker_Check_Failure` — mock checker returns false → `ConsecutiveFail` increments, `Healthy` becomes false after threshold\n- [ ] `TestBackendHealthChecker_Check_ResetOnSuccess` — after failures, success resets `ConsecutiveFail` to 0\n- [ ] `TestBackendHealthChecker_Check_ResetOnFailure` — after successes, failure resets `ConsecutiveSuccess` to 0\n- [ ] `TestBackendHealthChecker_Check_Concurrent` — concurrent `Check` calls are thread-safe (no race)\n- [ ] `TestDefaultHealthChecker` — verify `defaultHealthChecker` constructs `/health` path and checks 2xx status (use httptest server)\n\n## T-2: router/errors.go — Custom Error Types\n\n- [ ] `TestSessionNotFoundError_Error` — `Error()` returns `\"session \\\"<id>\\\" not found\"`\n- [ ] `TestNewSessionNotFoundError` — constructor sets `SessionID` field\n- [ ] `TestSandboxTemplateNotFoundError_Error` — `Error()` returns `\"sandbox template \\\"<ns>\\\"/<\\\"name\\\"> (kind=<kind>) not found\"`\n- [ ] `TestNewSandboxTemplateNotFoundError` — constructor sets Namespace, Name, Kind fields\n- [ ] `TestSessionTerminatedError_Error` — `Error()` returns `\"session \\\"<id>\\\" has been terminated\"`\n- [ ] `TestNewSessionTerminatedError` — constructor sets `SessionID` field\n\n## T-3: router/health.go — Health Endpoints\n\n- [ ] `TestHandleHealthLive` — returns 200 with `{\"status\": \"alive\"}`\n- [ ] `TestHandleHealthReady_WithSessionManager` — returns 200 with `{\"status\": \"ready\"}` when `sessionManager` is set\n- [ ] `TestHandleHealthReady_NoSessionManager` — returns 503 with `{\"status\": \"not ready\", \"error\": \"session manager not available\"}` when `sessionManager` is nil\n\n## T-4: router/loadbalancer.go — Load Balancers\n\n- [ ] `TestRoundRobinBalancer_Select_EmptyBackends` — returns `ErrNoHealthyBackend` for empty slice\n- [ ] `TestRoundRobinBalancer_Select_AllUnhealthy` — returns `ErrNoHealthyBackend` when all backends unhealthy\n- [ ] `TestRoundRobinBalancer_Select_SingleHealthy` — selects the single healthy backend\n- [ ] `TestRoundRobinBalancer_Select_RoundRobin` — cycles through healthy backends in order across multiple calls\n- [ ] `TestRoundRobinBalancer_Select_SkipUnhealthy` — skips unhealthy backends during rotation\n- [ ] `TestRoundRobinBalancer_Select_Concurrent` — concurrent `Select` calls are thread-safe\n- [ ] `TestLeastConnectionsBalancer_Select_EmptyBackends` — returns `ErrNoHealthyBackend` for empty slice\n- [ ] `TestLeastConnectionsBalancer_Select_AllUnhealthy` — returns `ErrNoHealthyBackend` when all unhealthy\n- [ ] `TestLeastConnectionsBalancer_Select_MinConnections` — selects backend with fewest connections\n- [ ] `TestLeastConnectionsBalancer_IncDec` — `Inc` increases connection count, `Dec` decreases\n- [ ] `TestLeastConnectionsBalancer_Inc_NewURL` — `Inc` initializes counter for unknown URL\n- [ ] `TestLeastConnectionsBalancer_Dec_UnknownURL` — `Dec` on unknown URL is a no-op (no panic)\n- [ ] `TestLeastConnectionsBalancer_Select_Concurrent` — concurrent `Select`/`Inc`/`Dec` calls are thread-safe\n\n## T-5: router/router.go — Router Implementation\n\n- [ ] `TestNewRouter` — creates router with empty routes map and assigned load balancer\n- [ ] `TestRouter_AddRoute` — adds route, subsequent `ServeHTTP` matches path\n- [ ] `TestRouter_AddRoute_EmptyPattern` — empty pattern is a no-op (no error, no route added)\n- [ ] `TestRouter_AddRoute_Duplicate` — adding same pattern twice is a no-op (no error)\n- [ ] `TestRouter_RemoveRoute` — removes route, subsequent `ServeHTTP` returns 404\n- [ ] `TestRouter_RemoveRoute_NonExistent` — removing non-existent route is a no-op\n- [ ] `TestRouter_ServeHTTP_NotFound` — unknown path returns 404\n- [ ] `TestRouter_ServeHTTP_UnhealthyBackend` — returns 503 with \"backend unhealthy\"\n- [ ] `TestRouter_ServeHTTP_LoadBalancerError` — returns 502 when load balancer returns error\n\n## T-6: router/proxy.go — Proxy & Invoke Handlers\n\n- [ ] `TestHandleGetSandboxError_APIStatus` — extracts code and message from `apierrors.APIStatus`\n- [ ] `TestHandleGetSandboxError_APIStatus_ZeroCode` — defaults to 500 when status code is 0\n- [ ] `TestHandleGetSandboxError_APIStatus_InternalServerError` — overrides message to \"internal server error\" for 500\n- [ ] `TestHandleGetSandboxError_GenericError` — returns 500 with \"internal server error\" for non-APIStatus errors\n- [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_EntryPointMatch` — selects entry point matching invocation path prefix\n- [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_NoMatchFallback` — falls back to first entry point when no prefix match\n- [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_NoEntryPoints` — returns 404 with \"no entry point found for sandbox\"\n- [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_ProtocolPrefix` — prepends protocol to endpoint when missing `://`\n- [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_DefaultHTTP` — defaults to `http://` when no protocol specified\n- [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_InvalidURL` — returns 500 with \"invalid target URL\" for unparseable URL\n- [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_ForwardedHeaders` — sets `X-Forwarded-Host`, `X-Forwarded-Proto`, `X-Forwarded-For`\n- [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_ExistingForwardedFor` — appends client IP to existing `X-Forwarded-For`\n- [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_JWTForSandbox` — generates and sets JWT `Authorization` header for Sandbox kind\n- [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_JWTForSandboxClaim` — generates and sets JWT `Authorization` header for SandboxClaim kind\n- [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_NoJWTForAgentRuntime` — does not set JWT header for AgentRuntime kind\n- [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_SessionIDHeader` — sets `x-agentcube-session-id` in response via `ModifyResponse`\n- [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_ErrorHandler_ConnectionRefused` — returns 502 with \"sandbox unreachable\"\n- [ ] `TestForwardToSandbox_ErrorHandler_Timeout` — returns 504 with \"sandbox timeout\"\n- [ ] `TestHandleInvoke_SessionNotFound` — returns 404 when `GetSandboxBySession` returns `SessionNotFoundError`\n- [ ] `TestHandleInvoke_TemplateNotFound` — returns 404 when `GetSandboxBySession` returns `SandboxTemplateNotFoundError`\n- [ ] `TestHandleInvoke_StoreError` — delegates to `handleGetSandboxError` for other store errors\n- [ ] `TestHandleInvoke_NoEntryPoints` — returns 404 when sandbox has no entry points\n- [ ] `TestHandleInvoke_UpdateLastActivity` — calls `UpdateSessionLastActivity` before and after forwarding\n- [ ] `TestHandleAgentInvoke` — calls `handleInvoke` with `AgentRuntimeKind`\n- [ ] `TestHandleCodeInterpreterInvoke` — calls `handleInvoke` with `CodeInterpreterKind`\n\n## T-7: router/session_manager.go — Session Manager\n\n- [ ] `TestNewSessionManager_MissingEnvVar` — returns error when `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` is not set\n- [ ] `TestNewSessionManager_Success` — creates manager with store client, workload URL, and HTTP client\n- [ ] `TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession_WithSessionID` — calls `storeClient.GetSandbox` and returns result\n- [ ] `TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession_NotFound` — returns `SessionNotFoundError` when store returns `ErrNotFound`\n- [ ] `TestSessionManager_GetSandboxBySession_NoSessionID` — calls `createSandbox` then `CreateSession` when sessionID is empty\n- [ ] `TestSessionManager_CreateSession` — calls `storeClient.StoreSandbox` with sessionID and info\n- [ ] `TestSessionManager_UpdateSession` — calls `storeClient.UpdateSandbox`\n- [ ] `TestSessionManager_DeleteSession` — calls `storeClient.DeleteSandboxBySessionID`\n- [ ] `TestSessionManager_UpdateLastActivity` — calls `storeClient.UpdateSessionLastActivity` with `time.Now()`\n- [ ] `TestSessionManager_ListSessions` — calls and returns `storeClient.ListSandboxes`\n- [ ] `TestSessionManager_CreateSandbox_AgentRuntime` — POSTs to `/v1/agent-runtime` for AgentRuntime kind\n- [ ] `TestSessionManager_CreateSandbox_CodeInterpreter` — POSTs to `/v1/code-interpreter` for CodeInterpreter kind\n- [ ] `TestSessionManager_CreateSandbox_DefaultKind` — defaults to `/v1/agent-runtime` for unknown kind\n- [ ] `TestSessionManager_CreateSandbox_NonOKResponse` — returns `SandboxTemplateNotFoundError` on non-200 response\n- [ ] `TestSessionManager_CreateSandbox_EmptySessionID` — returns error when response has empty session ID\n- [ ] `TestSessionManager_CreateSandbox_DecodeError` — returns error on malformed JSON response\n- [ ] `TestSessionManager_CreateSandbox_Success` — returns populated `SandboxInfo` with entry points on success\n\n## T-8: store/store.go — Store Interface & Singleton\n\n- [ ] `TestStorage_InterfaceCompliance` — `var _ store.Store = (*redisStore)(nil)` and `(*valkeyStore)(nil)` compile (interface compliance assertion)\n- [ ] `TestErrNotFound` — `ErrNotFound` error message is \"sandbox not found\"\n\n## T-9: picod/types.go — Constants & Types\n\n- [ ] `TestConstants_Values` — `TimeoutExitCode == 124`, `MaxBodySize == 32<<20`, `PublicKeyEnvVar == \"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"`, `maxFileMode == 0777`\n- [ ] `TestExecuteRequest_RequiredBinding` — JSON binding validates `command` field is required\n- [ ] `TestUploadFileRequest_RequiredBindin